cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.RO 

This paper deals with natural language processing and computer vision to interpret navigation instructions based on a real, dense, urban map. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a neural architecture for the task, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also investigates which aspects of the neural architecture are important for the task success, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Learning). The paper uses visual sensors to provide knowledge of the environment, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with navigation, which involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) another possible category.
